<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">the thieves.  However it was <span class="AddHand-author">soon</span> discovered that it was a false alarm &#8212; caused by some persons who were only leading away their <span class="AddHand-editors">[own]</span> horses<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  We experienced a heavy fall of rain which left a milion of musquitoes to destroy our rest.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday 29<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This morning our horses which broke loose in the night were missing<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  A young man brought them back<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he rain having ceased We saddled and Set out leaving all the little things we could spare to our generous host the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Black Cat</span> who received them with gratitude<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  After bidding a final adieu to the mandanes we directed our course through the wood where we observed an amazing quantity of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Poires</span>.  The mandans being surrounded with Enemies particularly at this season the women dare not venture out to gather fruit even in the vicinity of the Villages<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  For the Villages on the North Side lay under a great disadvantage being lined with thick wood and brushes for two miles deep which afford an opportunity for the enemy to approach<span class="DelHand-author">ed</span> unperceived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> even a single Sioux has been known to secret himself for several days among these trees until a favourable moment offered when</p>
